propertyDescriptions.Data File Title: The name or title of the Data File being described
propertyDescriptions.Data File Identifier: Information about the globally unique and persistent identifier used to identify and optionally access (meta)data of the data file being described.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Content: Information about conceptual content of the Data File
propertyDescriptions.Data File Version: Version of the resource being described.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Language: Language in which the data file being described is provided.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Subjects and Keywords: Concepts (keywords, classification, or free text terms) that define the data file or purpose (subjects which can be addressed) using the data file.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Description: Summary of the Data File and its contents.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Creator: An entity that brought into existence the data file being described. Creators can be people or organizations.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Related Resource: Information about resource related to the data file or other entity being described.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Contributor: An entity that contributed in bringing into existence the data file being described. Contributors can be people or organizations.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Rights: Way in which the data file may or may not be accessed and used.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Date: Relevant date related to the data file being described.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Parent Study: The research study for which this data file was created.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Funding Source: The sources of funding that enabled and drove the creation of the data file. (Non-monetary sources are described under Contributor.)
propertyDescriptions.Data File Distribution: Details about the distribution for this individual public presentation of the data file (if part of the Distribution metadata), or for all the public presentations of the data file being described (if part of the data file metadata).
propertyDescriptions.Data Characteristics Summary: Characteristics of the data within the data file, particularly of the cohorts in the data file.
propertyDescriptions.Data Source: Physical or conceptual entity (agent) that creates the data streams that make up the described data file. The data source may or may not be associated with a fixed location; for example, a series of discrete sensors deployed over time to a single location may be considered a single data source in some systems.
propertyDescriptions.Data Stream: A collection of one or more variable records that make up this data set. Each data stream originates from a single data source (e.g., sensor, process, or person). A data stream can grow over time.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Creation Process: Process (activity) used to make the data file or product.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Temporal Coverage: A temporal description that specifies the temporal coverage of the data contained within the data file associated with this metadata.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Spatial Coverage: A geospatial description that specifies the geographical coverage of the data contained within the data file associated with this metadata.
propertyDescriptions.Data File Elevation Coverage: The elevation  covered by the data file being described.
propertyDescriptions.Auxiliary Metadata: Information about the data file or metadata submission that does not fit into the other categories

Type Of Content.schema:name: Type Of Content
Type Of Content.schema:description:
The kind of content that the data file contains.  Data files are either text or non-text (binary) representations of datasets, images etc.  This field describes the conceptual type of the thing that is represented by the data file.

In most cases the value of this field will "Data Set" but other common types include "Audiovisual", "Data Stream", "Image"

Data File Identifier.title: Element(Data File Identifier)

Identifier Type.schema:name: Identifier Type
Identifier Type.schema:description:
The identifier type used to identify the resource being described.

This need not be provided if the identifier is either a DOI that begins with "doi:" or "http://doi.org/", or it is a URL that begins with either "http://" or "https://"
Identifier Type.title: Field(Identifier Type)

Identifier.schema:name: Identifier
Identifier.schema:description:
A globally unique string that identifies the Data File being described. It is typically a DOI (Digital Object Identifier) or URL (Uniform Resource Locator, that is, Web address). The identifier is typically generated by data providers or data publishers who wish to have a citable and Web-accessible resource.

Example DOIs are "doi:10.1000/182" or "http://doi.org/10.1000/182", both of which identify the DOI Handbook, which has a DOI of 10.1000/182

See also:  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_object_identifier
Identifier.title: Field(Identifier)

SHA256 digest.schema:name: SHA256 digest
SHA256 digest.schema:description:
A SHA256 digest of the Data File contents.  This is a 64 characters long hexadecimal string.  

As an example, the SHA256 digest of "RADx Data Hub" is ebff8d3da88b292622d3bfc36bdac4c4537ddc56cb07f344c5223d6b6f9cd011
SHA256 digest.title: Field(SHA256 digest)

File Name.title: Field(File Name )
